\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"=== SECTOR logistics STATUS ===\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nFile: job/sectors/recruiter-logistics.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPhase: coverage | Companies: 53 | Unpopulated: 6 | Missing descriptions: 42 | Below 10 contacts: 53\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRecruiters: 116\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNext work:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0062 P1 DoorDash | recs=1 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0060 P2 Lyft | recs=1 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0063 P2 Instacart | recs=1 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0074 P2 Expedia Group | recs=2 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0167 P2 Royal Caribbean Group | recs=1 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0075 P3 Booking Holdings | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0165 P3 Ryder System | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0166 P3 Carnival Corporation | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0173 P3 World Kinect (World Fuel Services) | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0175 P3 Watsco | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0181 P3 Brightline | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0192 P3 Boatsetter | recs=2 | desc=yes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC0195 P3 Marriott Vacations Worldwide | recs=2 | desc=yes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nC1050 P3 FedEx | recs=3 | desc=no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n=== SECTOR_BATCH_COMPLETE logistics 11 24 6 42 ===\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\njob/swarm/codex-sector-logs/logistics.jsonl:65:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_33\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent_message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"=== SECTOR_BATCH_COMPLETE logistics 11 24 6 42 ===\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\njob/swarm/codex-sector-logs/logistics.jsonl:72:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' job/swarm/sectors/logistics.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Codex Sector Worker — Logistics / Mobility\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Assignment**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Sector key: `logistics`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Working file: `job/sectors/recruiter-logistics.json`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Companies owned by this sector: 53\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- You may edit **only** `job/sectors/recruiter-logistics.json`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not edit `job/recruiter.json`, UI copies, other sector files, or shared docs.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not run the merge script. The orchestrator runs merges centrally after each batch to avoid write races.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Mission**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPopulate this sector with useful outreach data without repeating completed work:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Add or improve `company.description` for every company you touch, including companies that already have recruiters.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Populate empty `recruiters[]` arrays where credible public LinkedIn/web evidence exists.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Keep existing recruiter entries unless you can clearly tell they are stale or wrong.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. After coverage is complete, deepen companies to a maximum of 10 contacts each.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n5. After existing companies are deepened, add more companies in this sector, prioritizing Miami / South Florida and San Jose / Silicon Valley.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Company Description Standard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nEvery touched company should have a concise description:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- 18-35 words, one sentence.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Say what the company actually does and where it fits in the sector.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Prefer concrete products, customers, or technical domain over marketing language.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Mention SWE/AI relevance only when it is natural.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not invent facts. If public data is thin, use a conservative description based on the company category and careers/company page.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nExample:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"NVIDIA designs GPUs, AI accelerators, networking hardware, and software platforms used across data centers, gaming, autonomous systems, and applied machine learning.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Recruiter Standard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMinimum viable per company:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Strong signals: add 2-3 current, relevant recruiters or talent partners, then move on.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Weak signals: 1 recruiter is acceptable; for startups or thin teams, use a founder, CTO, VP Engineering, Head of Engineering, hiring manager, or technical lead.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Prefer university, campus, emerging talent, early-career, intern, new grad, SWE, AI, ML, or technical recruiting titles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- In bolster mode, technical members who are publicly hiring for their team are valid, especially for internship, new-grad, SWE, AI, ML, data, infrastructure, or product engineering roles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- US-based or clearly US-hiring people are preferred.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Never add more than 10 contacts to a company. If it already has 10 or more, skip it unless correcting stale data.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use only public professional information. Do not scrape aggressively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRecruiter object schema:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"linkedin_url\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"email\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"location\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"focus_area\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"connected\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"messaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"responded\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"date_contacted\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Batch Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do exactly one batch per Codex invocation, then exit after printing the marker.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Batch size: 8-14 companies.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 1 Coverage: prioritize companies with empty `recruiters[]`; then companies missing `description`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 2 Bolster: once every existing company has a description and at least one contact, improve companies with fewer than 10 contacts. Add recruiters first, then technical hiring managers / founders / team leads who are visibly hiring interns or early-career technical talent.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 3 Expansion: once the existing sector list is reasonably deepened, add 3-8 new companies in this sector per batch. Prioritize Miami, Fort Lauderdale, Boca Raton, West Palm Beach, San Jose, Santa Clara, Sunnyvale, Mountain View, Palo Alto, and nearby startup/tech hubs. Add descriptions and at least 1-3 contacts for new companies where possible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Spend roughly 5-8 minutes per company on average.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use web search in parallel where possible:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"university recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"campus recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"early career recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"talent acquisition\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") (intern OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"new grad\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR SWE OR software) LinkedIn -inurl:jobs`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Recruiter at <Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"University Recruiter at <Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" site:linkedin.com/in`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (recruiter OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"talent partner\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"hiring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") (internship OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"campus recruiting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"university hiring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") 2025 OR 2026`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Required Start Status Command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\