any category and careers/company page.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nExample:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"NVIDIA designs GPUs, AI accelerators, networking hardware, and software platforms used across data centers, gaming, autonomous systems, and applied machine learning.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Recruiter Standard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMinimum viable per company:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Strong signals: add 2-3 current, relevant recruiters or talent partners, then move on.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Weak signals: 1 recruiter is acceptable; for startups or thin teams, use a founder, CTO, VP Engineering, Head of Engineering, hiring manager, or technical lead.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Prefer university, campus, emerging talent, early-career, intern, new grad, SWE, AI, ML, or technical recruiting titles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- In bolster mode, technical members who are publicly hiring for their team are valid, especially for internship, new-grad, SWE, AI, ML, data, infrastructure, or product engineering roles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- US-based or clearly US-hiring people are preferred.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Never add more than 10 contacts to a company. If it already has 10 or more, skip it unless correcting stale data.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use only public professional information. Do not scrape aggressively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRecruiter object schema:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"linkedin_url\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"email\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"location\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"focus_area\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"connected\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"messaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"responded\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": false,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"date_contacted\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Batch Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do exactly one batch per Codex invocation, then exit after printing the marker.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Batch size: 8-14 companies.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 1 Coverage: prioritize companies with empty `recruiters[]`; then companies missing `description`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 2 Bolster: once every existing company has a description and at least one contact, improve companies with fewer than 10 contacts. Add recruiters first, then technical hiring managers / founders / team leads who are visibly hiring interns or early-career technical talent.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Phase 3 Expansion: once the existing sector list is reasonably deepened, add 3-8 new companies in this sector per batch. Prioritize Miami, Fort Lauderdale, Boca Raton, West Palm Beach, San Jose, Santa Clara, Sunnyvale, Mountain View, Palo Alto, and nearby startup/tech hubs. Add descriptions and at least 1-3 contacts for new companies where possible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Spend roughly 5-8 minutes per company on average.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use web search in parallel where possible:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"university recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"campus recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"early career recruiter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"talent acquisition\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") (intern OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"new grad\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR SWE OR software) LinkedIn -inurl:jobs`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Recruiter at <Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"University Recruiter at <Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" site:linkedin.com/in`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<Company>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (recruiter OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"talent partner\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"hiring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") (internship OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"campus recruiting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" OR \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"university hiring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") 2025 OR 2026`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Required Start Status Command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nnode -e '\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst fs=require(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"); const d=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"job/sectors/recruiter-energy.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"utf8\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"));\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst companies=d.companies||[];\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst unpop=companies.filter(c=>!(c.recruiters||[]).length);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst missing=companies.filter(c=>!String(c.description||\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").trim());\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst under10=companies.filter(c=>(c.recruiters||[]).length<10);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconst phase=(unpop.length||missing.length) ? \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" : (under10.length ? \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"bolster\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" : \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"expand\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\");\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconsole.log(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"=== SECTOR energy STATUS ===\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\");\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconsole.log(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"File: job/sectors/recruiter-energy.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\");\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconsole.log(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Phase:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", phase, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| Companies:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", companies.length, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| Unpopulated:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", unpop.length, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| Missing descriptions:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", missing.length, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| Below 10 contacts:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", under10.length);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconsole.log(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Recruiters:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", companies.reduce((s,c)=>s+(c.recruiters||[]).length,0));\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconsole.log(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Next work:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\");\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n[...unpop, ...missing.filter(c=>!unpop.some(u=>u.id===c.id)), ...under10.filter(c=>!unpop.some(u=>u.id===c.id)&&!missing.some(m=>m.id===c.id))]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  .sort((a,b)=>(a.priority-b.priority)||a.id.localeCompare(b.id))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  .slice(0,14)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  .forEach(c=>console.log(c.id, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"P\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"+c.priority, c.name, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| recs=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"+((c.recruiters||[]).length), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"| desc=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"+(String(c.description||\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").trim() ? \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"yes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" : \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")));\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Edit Pattern\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse a small Node script or safe JSON-aware edit against `job/sectors/recruiter-energy.json` only. Preserve JSON formatting with two-space indentation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nBefore adding a recruiter/contact:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Check the existing `recruiters[]` array and do not duplicate a person or LinkedIn URL.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Keep current useful entries; append only net-new contacts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nBefore adding a new company:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Search all sector files and canonical JSON by exact company name so you do not duplicate existing work.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Reserve IDs with `node job/scripts/allocate-company-ids.js <count>`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use this company shape:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"C1252\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Company Name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"category\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"EV / Energy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sector\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"energy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\